## ROLES & PERMISSIONS — ALWAYS CHECK

There are exactly 9 roles in KMSAR:
1. `super_admin`     — Full system access
2. `ovpri_admin`     — University-wide approval and reporting
3. `cdaic_admin`     — Same as ovpri_admin
4. `college_dean`    — Endorse/return for own college only
5. `unit_head`       — Same as college_dean but scoped to unit
6. `faculty`         — Submit and update own research
7. `co_author`       — View + optionally upload on shared research
8. `registrar`       — Read-only, approved research only
9. `viewer`          — Read-only, published summaries only

When writing any controller method that touches research data:
- Always apply the corresponding Policy — never skip authorization
- Always scope queries to the user's visible data — never return all records without role check
- Dean can only see `mother_college_id = auth()->user()->college_id`
- Faculty can only see own research or research where they are a co-author
- OVPRI/CDAIC can see everything

