## DATABASE RULES

- Always use Eloquent — no raw SQL with string interpolation
- Always add appropriate indexes: foreign keys, status columns, frequently filtered columns
- Use soft deletes on `research` and `documents` tables — `SoftDeletes` trait
- Use JSON columns for `sdg_tags` (array of integers 1–17)
- `audit_logs` table is append-only — never update or delete audit records
- Use `DB::transaction()` for any operation that touches more than one table
- Always eager load relationships to prevent N+1 queries — `with(['primaryAuthor', 'motherCollege'])`
- Use `cursor()` for large dataset iteration in exports — never `get()` on unbounded result sets

---

## WHAT TO NEVER DO

- Never use `{!! !!}` without explicit sanitization
- Never store uploaded files in `public/` or `storage/app/public/`
- Never check `$user->role === 'dean'` inline — always use Policies/Gates
- Never update `research.approval_stage` directly — always use `ApprovalService`
- Never call Mail::send() or Notification::send() synchronously inside a transaction
- Never use jQuery — Alpine.js only
- Never use React, Vue, Livewire, or Inertia — Blade + Alpine.js only
- Never build a standalone HTML page — always extend `layouts.app`
- Never use `$guarded = []` on models — always define explicit `$fillable`
- Never hardcode colors inline with `style=""` — use Tailwind or KMSAR.css
- Never add emojis to UI — SVG icons only
- Never skip Form Request validation — all user input goes through Form Requests
- Never return all records without a scope — always apply role-based filtering
- Never commit `.env` to version control

