## AUF COLLEGES & PROGRAMS (Official — use these EXACTLY in seeders, dropdowns, and migrations)

There is a `programs` table in addition to `colleges`. Schema:
- `programs`: id, college_id (FK), code VARCHAR(30) UQ, name VARCHAR(200), is_active TINYINT(1), timestamps

### CollegeSeeder — exact data:
```php
CAMP → College of Allied Medical Professions
CAS  → College of Arts and Sciences
CBA  → College of Business and Accountancy
CCS  → College of Computer Studies
CCJE → College of Criminal Justice Education
CED  → College of Education
CEA  → College of Engineering
```

### ProgramSeeder — exact data per college:
```
CAMP: BSClinPhar, BSMT, BSOT, PHARM, BSPT, BSRT
CAS:  AB Com, BSBIO, BS Human Bio, BSPSY, SABPsych-MAPsych
CBA:  BSA, BSBA, BSHM, BSMA, BSTM
CCS:  BMMA, BSCS, BSIT
CCJE: BSCRM
CED:  BEEd, BSEd, BSNEd
CEA:  BSARCHI, BSCE, BSCOE, BS ECE
```

When generating any college dropdown, seeder, migration, factory, or filter —
always use EXACTLY these 7 colleges and their programs. Never invent or abbreviate.
The `users` table has a `college_id` FK and optionally a `program_id` FK → programs.id.
Faculty belong to one college and one program.
